page.title: 15Southampton Bird Life
page.content: In our part of the D-Block we have watched the bird life. We did a survey to find the most common birds. They were:- 1{House Sparrow}2{Starling}3 {Blackbird}4{Mistle Thrush}5{Robin}6 {Chaffinch}7{Dunnock}8{Carrion Crow}9 {Song Thrush}10{Black-headed Gull . "I watched some{swifts}flying over { {Nursling}village. They were ducking and diving and doing loops. They flew very fast feeding on insects." "At{Test Valley Nature Reserve}I saw a small bird with black on its face, a long tail, and light brown wings. It had a pale grey head, a whitish throat and a yellow bill. I found out it was a male{Bearded Tit}." "My favourite bird is the{Kestrel.}I see one hovering over the M271. Its head quite still while its wings flap. Its powerful eyes spot something, and it swoops onto the bank for its prey."
